readings and the performances

00:01:54.740 --> 00:01:56.390
and then our conversation, I want

00:01:56.390 --> 00:01:58.900
to give us just a little
bit of context.

00:01:58.900 --> 00:02:01.680
In the excellent reference
book of Poet's Glossary,

00:02:01.680 --> 00:02:07.790
Edward Hirsch writes, "Song was
originally inseparable from poetry.

00:02:07.790 --> 00:02:12.160
They were one in the same and
poems were meant to be chanted

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:16.500
and sung sustained
by oral tradition."

00:02:16.500 --> 00:02:19.330
Poetry is still considered
song in many parts

00:02:19.330 --> 00:02:22.260
of the world whether
it is presented with

00:02:22.260 --> 00:02:24.640
or without musical accompaniment.

00:02:24.640 --> 00:02:28.550
The musical element is
so intrinsic to poetry

00:02:28.550 --> 00:02:33.930
that one never forgets its origin
in musical expression in singing,

00:02:33.930 --> 00:02:38.270
chanting and recitation
to musical accompaniment.

00:02:38.270 --> 00:02:40.410
With that in mind please join me

00:02:40.410 --> 00:02:42.510
in welcoming Joy Harjo
and A.B. Spellman.

