00:38:25.410 --> 00:38:29.230
It opened up that door for me.

00:38:29.230 --> 00:38:31.270
&gt;&gt; A.B. Spellman: Yeah, well music

00:38:31.270 --> 00:38:33.630
and poetry has been
there in the beginning.

00:38:33.630 --> 00:38:40.520
In fact, I've always thought
that prosody was an expression

00:38:40.520 --> 00:38:45.060
of the root of music in poetry
that the poets needed a mnemonic

00:38:45.060 --> 00:38:50.230
to be able to remember so they
had to develop forms to go with it

00:38:50.230 --> 00:38:52.060 position:56%
and these forms were shaped by song.

00:38:52.060 --> 00:38:53.710
I've always thought
that's been the case,

00:38:53.710 --> 00:38:56.760
but among African American poets
the concern has always been there.

00:38:56.760 --> 00:39:01.560
Langston Hughes, for example, was
very much committed to having,

00:39:01.560 --> 00:39:04.890
